A life insurance company has asked an Oklahoma judge to decide whether they should be forced to hand over $20,000 to a teen accused of murdering his entire family in order to cash in on the policy.

Deeply indebted, self-proclaimed shopaholic Alan Hruby, 19, confessed he gunned down his mother, father and sister in October in the hope of paying off a $3,000 loan shark debt.

As Hruby faces a potential death penalty, American Fidelity Assurance Co. this week petitioned a judge to disqualify him from receiving the policy proceeds policy say he was desperate enough to slay his for.

