The company says it can deny Hruby the money because of his alleged role in his family members' death, but needs the judge's approval. 

The pay out would come from two American Fidelity policies held by Hruby's rural newspaper publisher father, NewsOK reports.

His father, John Hruby, named his wife Tinker as the main beneficiary. In the event of her death, the money was to go to Alan and his little sister Katherine Hruby, 17.

Authorities say Hruby admitted he murdered his family to become the sole heir after he was cut off by them financially.

